leadership_approach|process_vision_people_results|paired|Read Process and Vision as a working pair. Let the steps, standards, and handovers are clear enough to follow sit alongside the work has a reason that connects today to what comes next, then bring in People and Results when the work needs more range.|Process and Vision together connect sequence, standards, and dependable structure with direction, meaning, and future consequence. This can make the work easier to understand, carry, and sustain.|The pair can take too much space when People or Results is needed to complete the picture. The risk is a context mismatch: the work may need decision, ownership, and follow-through sooner than the pair expects.|Bring in People when trust, communication, inclusion, or commitment needs more direct attention. Bring in Results when the work needs a firmer decision, owner, or visible next move. The pair stays steadier when these checks arrive before the answer feels settled.|Process and Vision carry the centre; Results keeps the work rounded.|active|leadership_approach::process_vision_people_results::paired
leadership_approach|process_vision_people_results|graduated|Read the order as a stepped pattern of influence: Process, then Vision, then People, with Results added deliberately. The closing point is to follow that order while still making room for decision, ownership, and follow-through.|The rank order gives the work a clear movement from sequence, standards, and dependable structure through direction, meaning, and future consequence and trust, communication, and shared commitment. Results adds the final range when the situation calls for decision, ownership, and follow-through.|The sequence can become too closed when later signals are left until the situation has already tightened. Results matters when the work now needs decision, ownership, and follow-through.|Bring in Results when the work needs a firmer decision, owner, or visible next move. Treat it as part of the full order rather than an emergency move.|Follow the order, then make space for Results before the work closes in.|active|leadership_approach::process_vision_people_results::graduated
